main event: A radar operator detected an unidentified object over Wichita, Kansas in 1950.
interesting points: The object was tracked on radar for approximately 1 minute.
The object was observed to travel on a course between 210-275 degrees.
The radar operator could not definitively identify the object as an aircraft.
No photographs were taken during the sighting.
The report indicates this was a Ground-Radar observation rather than a visual sighting.
